"# Step 2

确定好 Warudo 主窗口想要处于的显示器  
（以下称为显示器 A）

确定你想要显示在画面中的显示器  
（以下称为显示器 B）

确定后**请勿更改**，否则需要重新调整参数。"

"# Step 2

（如果 显示器 A = 显示器 B，可跳过该步骤）

将你的鼠标放置在显示器 B 的【**左上角**】。
将其数值的【**相反数**】填写在右边。

## →

例如，如果鼠标位于左上角时候，Output 为  
（1920, -1080）  
则填写：  
偏移 X = -1920  
偏移 Y = +1080

如果填写正确，鼠标位于显示器 B 的左上角时，Output 应该为 (0, 0)。"

"# Step 4

在【Prop - Drawing Screen】中选择 【显示器 B】作为内容显示。

# Step 5

（初次尝试建议跳过该步骤）

现在你可以使用【新手向导】调整角色，环境，动捕，以及角色以及屏幕的位置了。

对于不同的角色，你很可能需要调整【Anchor - Right Hand IK】的位置，来使得角色更好地握住笔。

并且您需要在运动捕捉的设置中**禁用手指相关的摆锤物理！**


# Step 6

分别调整【Prop - Calibration Border】 的【缩放比例】中的 X 和 Y，使得屏幕刚好处于红框的 **内边缘** 。

注意：每次都需要先解锁【等比例缩放】再调整【缩放比例】。"
"# Step 7\n\n最后，你可以隐藏【Prop - Calibration Border】（不要删除）"

"# 注意事项

你可能需要调整动捕中的【镜像追踪】或者【反转双手】来选择你喜欢的追踪方式。


如果你想更换显示器 A 或者显示器 B 的选择，都需要重新进行 Step 2 ~ 6。

你可以调整【Prop - Drawing Screen】的厚度或者开启并调整【Prop - Tablet】的大小来进一步增加真实感。
"

"# Step 2

Determine the monitor you want the Warudo main window to locate.  
(called Monitor A)

Determine the monitor you want to be display in Warudo.  
(called Monitor B)

After confirming, **do not change**, otherwise you will need to re-adjust the parameters."

"# Step 2

(If Monitor A = Monitor B, you can skip this step)

Place your mouse at the **upper left corner** of Monitor B. Fill in the **opposite value** on the right node.

## →

e.g. If the Output is (1920, -1080) when the mouse is at the upper left corner, fill in:  
Offset X = -1920  
Offset Y = +1080

If the offset is correct, the output should be (0, 0) when the mouse is at the upper left corner of Monitor B."

"# Step 3

# →

Fill in the resolution (in pixel) of Monitor B in the right node.

Common 16:9 resolutions:  
1080p: 1920 × 1080  
2K: 2560 × 1440  
4K: 3840 × 2160"

"# Step 4

Select **[Monitor B]** as the Content-Display in **[Prop - Drawing Screen]**.

# Step 5

(We recommend skipping this step for first try)

Now you can use the **[Onboarding Assistant]** to adjust the position of the character, environment, motion capture, and the position of the character and screen.

For different characters, you may need to adjust the position of **[Anchor - Right Hand IK]** to make the character hold the pen better.

And you need to **disable the finger pendulum physics in motion capture settings!**

# Step 6

Adjust the **X** and **Y** in the **[Scale]** of **[Prop - Calibration Border]** respectively. To make sure that the screen fits the **inner edge** of the red box as perfectly as possible.

Note: You need to unlock **[Uniform Scaling]** before adjusting **[Scale]** each time."
"# Step 7\n\nFinally, you can hide **[Prop - Calibration Border]** (do not delete)"

"# Things to note

You may need to change **[Mirrored Tracking]** or **[Invert Hands]** in the motion capture to choose the tracking method you prefer.

If you want to change the selection of Monitor A or Monitor B, you need to repeat Step 2–6.

You can adjust the thickness of **[Prop - Drawing Screen]** or enable and adjust the scale of **[Prop - Tablet]** to further increase the realism."
